"{\"abstract\":\"We present a generative probabilistic model of documents as sequences of sentences, and show that inference in it can lead to extraction of long-range latent discourse structure from a collection of documents. The approach is based on embedding sequences of sentences from longer texts into a 2- or 3-D spatial grids, in which one or two coordinates model smooth topic transitions, while the third captures the sequential nature of the modeled text. A significant advantage of our approach is that the learned models are naturally visualizable and interpretable, as semantic similarity and sequential structure are modeled along orthogonal directions in the grid. We show that the method is effective in capturing discourse structures in narrative text across multiple genres, including biographies, stories, and newswire reports. In particular, our method outperforms or is competitive with state-of-the-art generative approaches on tasks such as predicting the outcome of a story, and sentence ordering.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3284698\",\"name\":\"Shashank Srivastava\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3284698\"},{\"authorId\":\"1698689\",\"name\":\"N. Jojic\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1698689\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":51872769,\"doi\":\"10.18653/v1/P18-1211\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":true,\"paperId\":\"f9196480457bca23771da88d3f20ce177c8d036c\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1781337\",\"name\":\"Ziheng Lin\"},{\"authorId\":\"34789794\",\"name\":\"H. Ng\"},{\"authorId\":\"37596605\",\"name\":\"Min-Yen Kan\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"1fa3c7c81864bbdfab8fbefab470864646844ddb\",\"title\":\"Automatically Evaluating Text Coherence Using Discourse Relations\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1fa